.TH HSH 1 "11 August 2025" "v1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
hsh \-  A minimalist UNIX command-line interpreter written in C

.SH SYNOPSIS
In interactive mode:
.br
.B ./hsh
.RI [ arguments ]
.PP
In non-interactive mode:
.br
.B echo
.RI [ arguments ]
.B | ./hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
A minimalist UNIX command-line interpreter written in C.
It provides a basic environment to execute system commands, similar to the standard sh shell.
It supports both interactive and non-interactive modes.

.SH EXAMPLES
In interactive mode:

.nf
#cisfun$ ls
AUTHORS  builtin.c  executor.c  hsh  input.c  main.c  man_1_simple_shell  parser.c  path.c  prompt.c  README.md  shell.h  utils.c

#cisfun$ /bin/ls
AUTHORS  builtin.c  executor.c  hsh  input.c  main.c  man_1_simple_shell  parser.c  path.c  prompt.c  README.md  shell.h  utils.c

#cisfun$ exit
./shell: No such file or directory   # 'exit' not supported

#cisfun$ [Ctrl+D]
[Shell exits]
.fi

In non-interactive mode:

.nf
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
AUTHORS  builtin.c  executor.c  hsh  input.c  main.c  man_1_simple_shell  parser.c  path.c  prompt.c  README.md  shell.h  utils.c

$ cat test_ls_2
/bin/ls
/bin/ls

$ cat test_ls_2 | ./hsh
hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2
hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2
.fi


